{"info": {"author": "Frederic G. \u00d8stby", "author_email": "frederic.g.ostby@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "description": "# Okam Security\n\n[![Build Status](https://img.shields.io/travis/freost/okam-security/master.svg?style=flat)](https://travis-ci.org/freost/okam-security)\n\nA Python port of the [Mako](https://makoframework.com) (PHP framework) security library.\n\n## Usage\n\n### Key\n\nThe `Key` class allows you to generate, encode and decode keys that can be used for cryptographic purposes.\n\n```\nfrom okam.security import Key\n\n# Returns 32 random bytes, you can also pass the number of bytes you want to return\n\nkey = Key.generate()\n\n# Returns a hex representation of the random bytes prefixed by 'hex:'\n\nencoded = Key.encode(key)\n\n# Returns the random bytes that were encoded\n\nkey = Key.decode(key)\n\n# Returns a hex representation of 32 random bytes prefixed by 'hex:',\n# you can also pass the number of bytes you want to return\n\nencoded = Key.generate_encoded()\n```\n\n### Signer\n\nThe `Signer` class allows you to verify both the data integrity and the authenticity of strings. A HMAC (hash-based message authentication code) will be prepended to your string upon signing and stripped when validated.\n\n```\nfrom okam.security import Key\nfrom okam.security import Signer\n\nsigner = Signer(Key.generate())\n\n# Signs the string\n\nsigned = signer.sign('hello, world!')\n\n# Returns the original string if the string can be authenticated and False if not\n\nstring = signer.validate(signed)\n```\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/freost/okam-security", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "okam-security", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/okam-security/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/okam-security/", "project_urls": {"Bug Tracker": "https://github.com/freost/okam-security/issues", "Homepage": "https://github.com/freost/okam-security", "Source Code": "https://github.com/freost/okam-security"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/okam-security/0.1.1/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": ">=3.5", "summary": "A Python port of the Mako (PHP framework) security library.", "version": "0.1.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Okam Security</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/freost/okam-security\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Build Status\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/0a266d63e7d16c7e1dfc0f723bae8f4269abc8aa/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f7472617669732f6672656f73742f6f6b616d2d73656375726974792f6d61737465722e7376673f7374796c653d666c6174\"></a></p>\n<p>A Python port of the <a href=\"https://makoframework.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mako</a> (PHP framework) security library.</p>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<h3>Key</h3>\n<p>The <code>Key</code> class allows you to generate, encode and decode keys that can be used for cryptographic purposes.</p>\n<pre><code>from okam.security import Key\n\n# Returns 32 random bytes, you can also pass the number of bytes you want to return\n\nkey = Key.generate()\n\n# Returns a hex representation of the random bytes prefixed by 'hex:'\n\nencoded = Key.encode(key)\n\n# Returns the random bytes that were encoded\n\nkey = Key.decode(key)\n\n# Returns a hex representation of 32 random bytes prefixed by 'hex:',\n# you can also pass the number of bytes you want to return\n\nencoded = Key.generate_encoded()\n</code></pre>\n<h3>Signer</h3>\n<p>The <code>Signer</code> class allows you to verify both the data integrity and the authenticity of strings. A HMAC (hash-based message authentication code) will be prepended to your string upon signing and stripped when validated.</p>\n<pre><code>from okam.security import Key\nfrom okam.security import Signer\n\nsigner = Signer(Key.generate())\n\n# Signs the string\n\nsigned = signer.sign('hello, world!')\n\n# Returns the original string if the string can be authenticated and False if not\n\nstring = signer.validate(signed)\n</code></pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6184867, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "c58baaa14c3b57d6c9347bbd75f5fe3b", "sha256": "280fa7c559a0b2ade83dc4832318ae227bdbe18b3af09e443009b3f681e7ed37"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "okam_security-0.1.0-py3.7.egg", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "c58baaa14c3b57d6c9347bbd75f5fe3b", "packagetype": "bdist_egg", "python_version": "3.7", "requires_python": ">=3.5", "size": 3794, "upload_time": "2019-11-21T20:31:21", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-11-21T20:31:21.534722Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/6d/ac/7768c9e7f896f1c7c34beaad54fcea6a2b83e3270534a6e4187950d66752/okam_security-0.1.0-py3.7.egg", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "70bcbfb3eba394de24e7cf47c9f0266b", "sha256": "cf0881c05c15f9ff85d9fd6403ac2253e6c90e9e2bec9cccdb69ef3ff46c157f"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "okam_security-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "70bcbfb3eba394de24e7cf47c9f0266b", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.5", "size": 3248, "upload_time": "2019-11-21T20:31:18", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-11-21T20:31:18.121049Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/f6/36/f35d083715fc600367786e3c2d6dd67d339893cca16ba6e8a911f8f7d123/okam_security-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "375445bbd8d8687137f1c2acb7bb9784", "sha256": "6ca8c612721a92c57f55bc6f8c18b835d57960fcddd2c9bfff5ca6700a1131d9"}, "down